27/01/2005
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- During a visit to Skopje, a delegation representing ethnic Albanian local governments in southern Serbia requested the opening of new three border crossings with Macedonia. 
The delegation, which included top representatives of the Presevo and Bujanovac municipalities, held talks Wednesday (26 January) with Macedonian Prime Minister Vlado Buckovski. 
(Dnevnik - 27/01/05; A1 TV - 26/01/05)
